{
  "stem": "2533.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we knew that it's going to-- closer and closer, because when D-Day-- you know, the 6th of June, that was '44-- when we heard about it, and I saw they came in with the newspapers, I was in the country then with all of them, and they were talking amongst each other.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was pretending that I'm not listening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I knew, the D-Day, that was the beginning of the end.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I still can see their faces, how they looked at each other and they knew that that's no way out anymore.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after that, he built his house up again, and he came just to travel backwards and forwards to Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And just before the end of the war, the Germans demolished all the bridges on the River Main.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I think there was about five, because Frankfurt was divided.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "One part was called Sachsenhausen, and the other was Frankfurt [NON-ENGLISH], and passed Warsaw, like Prague.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was cut off, the electricity, the water.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They even managed to sink ships with food and clothing into the River Main where the port was because Hildemann was not far from the port, from the eastern port.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then the Americans came, and they demolished the bridges because they thought they wouldn't-- they had to come through.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But the Americans came another way-- I don't know, through [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They didn't come through [NON-ENGLISH], I don't know which way they came.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But the 27th of April, '45, the Americans were there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I wasn't in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I was in the country.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The country house was about maybe 20 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
